'''Tsurugi Shrine''' (劔神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Nogata|ja|直方市}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県}}, Japan. It holds the former shrine rank of {{ill|Village shrine|ja|村社}} under the pre-modern shrine ranking system.

== Enshrined Deities ==
* {{ill|Izanagi|ja|伊邪那岐大神}}
* {{ill|Izanami|ja|伊邪那美大神}}
* {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊}}
* {{ill|Iwasaku and Nesaku|ja|石折神}} (Iwasaku no Kami), {{ill|Nesaku|ja|根折神}} (Nesaku no Kami)
* {{ill|Iwatatsuno-o|ja|石筒之男神}} (Iwatatsuno-o no Kami)
* {{ill|Mikahayahi|ja|甕速日神}} (Mikahayahi no Kami)
* {{ill|Hihayahino-kami|ja|樋速日神}} (Hihayahino-kami)
* {{ill|Takemikazuchi|ja|建御雷之男神}} (Takemikazuchi no Kami), also known as Takefutsu no Kami and Toyofutsu no Kami
* {{ill|Kuraokami|ja|闇淤加美神}} (Kuraokami no Kami)
* {{ill|Kuramitsuha|ja|闇御津羽神}} (Kuramitsuha no Kami)

These deities are believed to have been formed from the blood that dripped from the sword during the purification of {{ill|Izanagi|ja|伊邪那岐大神}} after returning from the underworld.

== History ==
[[File:tsurugi003.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Torii gate]]

The shrine's origins are attributed to {{ill|Tadomichi no Mikoto|ja|田道命}}, the first {{ill|Tsukushi no Kuni no Miyatsuko|ja|筑紫国造}}, who is said to have led the Tsukushi Mononobe clan in worshiping the deities. His descendant Nagatahiko served as the shrine priest.

Originally called "Kuraji Daimyōjin," the shrine was located atop Mount Tenjō-dake in the Rokkatake range. During the {{ill|Muromachi period|ja|室町時代}}, {{ill|Ashikaga Yoshimitsu|ja|足利義満}} ordered the reconstruction of the shrine. In the {{ill|Sengoku period|ja|戦国時代}}, the local lord of Ryūgatake Castle, the {{ill|Sugi clan|ja|杉氏}}, revered the shrine and enshrined {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊}}, renaming it "Yatsurugi Ōkami."

In the {{ill|Edo period|ja|江戸時代}}, after a fire destroyed the shrine, it was relocated to its current site on "Kameoka." The shrine was rebuilt under the patronage of Lord {{ill|Kuroda Nagakiyo|ja|黒田長清}}. The current shrine structure was established with the support of local worshippers.

== Annual Events ==
* **April 18:** Spring Grand Festival
* **July 29:** Summer Purification Festival
* **October (Sunday):** Autumn Grand Festival (every 5 years, features a sacred procession)
* **December 18:** Harvest Festival (Niiname-sai)

== Access ==
* Located at 2565 Shimo-Shinnyū, Nogata City, Fukuoka Prefecture, Japan
* 15-minute walk from JR {{ill|Shinnyū Station|ja|新入駅}}
* Near Nishitetsu Bus "Shinnyū Honmura" bus stop
* 5-minute drive from {{ill|Kurate Interchange|ja|鞍手インターチェンジ}} on the {{ill|Kyushu Expressway|ja|九州自動車道}}

